 On Friday at about 16:00 a mini-bus collided with a truck on the N11 between Middelburg and Hendrina.
Nine of the people in the taxi burnt to death.  The taxi was reportedly heading to Als Mine when the incident happened.
The drivers of the taxi and truck were rushed to the hospital. The deceased have not been identified yet. Also read: Nine people burn to death in N11 accident On Saturday, emergency services also attended an accident on the R555 (Stoffberg Road), where a Hyundai and a Volkswagen collided.
At least three people were killed in the head-on collision that occurred at about 08:00.  The Hyundai was travelling to Stoffberg while the Volkswagen was heading to Middelburg.
The Hyundai was carrying two men and a woman, who died on impact. The driver of the Volkswagen and a passenger were rushed to the hospital for medical treatment.
The deceased have also not been identified. Also read: Three dead, two critical in Stoffberg collision On Monday morning at about 05:25 an accident involving a Toyota Hilux and an Isuzu occurred on the R555(old Witbank Road)
A passenger in the Isuzu was killed in the collision and the drivers of both vehicles were rushed the hospital for medical treatment.         The ferals need help #TrafficAlert: R555 closed, seven die in horrific crash Middelburg police officer arrested during Hawks operation  • Save our standby number (072 248 3855) and send us a WhatsApp message with the words “Add me” to be added to our broadcast list. • Like us on Facebook, follow us on Twitter and Instagram. • Subscribe to our YouTube channel. • Click on the link to subscribe to our bi-weekly newsletter via email. Contact our news room on our 24 hr standby number 072 248 3855, or send a mail to our editor tobie@mobserver.co.za